WEBVTT

00:03.796 --> 00:06.879
The lot will hold 1,000 cars.

00:06.966 --> 00:11.630
That’s at least 1,000 souls
that will be saved,
my sisters and brothers.

00:11.721 --> 00:13.677
[ All Exclaiming]
Hallelujah!

00:13.764 --> 00:17.552
As our Lord says,
“If you build it, they will come.”

00:17.643 --> 00:19.759
- [ Man ] That’s right.
- [Crowd Laughing]

00:19.854 --> 00:21.515
- The Lord spoke to me—
- [ Birds Squawking]

00:21.606 --> 00:23.813
and told me to build
his church...

00:23.900 --> 00:26.107
right here
on this sacred ground.

00:26.194 --> 00:28.059
The Lord spoke to him!

00:28.196 --> 00:29.561
Oh, God!
[Exclaiming]

00:29.655 --> 00:34.524
He told me to turn this refuse
into a heaven on earth.

00:34.660 --> 00:36.491
[ Man ]
All right!
[Woman ] Amen!

00:36.579 --> 00:38.865
[ Squawking ]

00:38.956 --> 00:40.787
So, we need all of you...

00:40.875 --> 00:43.742
to answer the call
of the Holy Spirit...

00:43.836 --> 00:46.794
and to open your heart
and your wallet.

00:46.881 --> 00:48.371
[ Crowd ]
Amen!

00:50.927 --> 00:53.384
- What is that?
- Why does he look like that?

00:53.471 --> 00:55.427
[ Man ]
Why is it blue?

00:55.514 --> 00:57.505
- [Woman Gasps ]
- They’re falling from the heavens.

00:57.600 --> 00:59.636
- [Woman ]
It’s a bird.
- [ Gasping ]

00:59.727 --> 01:01.763
- Are they sick?
- It’s dead!

01:01.896 --> 01:04.137
[ Man ]
There’s another one.
[Glass Shatters]

01:04.232 --> 01:06.143
Where are they coming from?

01:06.234 --> 01:08.850
- It’s a plague from God!
- What does this mean?

01:08.986 --> 01:10.692
[Woman Screams ]
Brothers and sisters,

01:10.780 --> 01:12.941
I’m sure there’s an explanation.

01:13.032 --> 01:15.239
- It’s God’s plan!
- Help us, Lord.

01:15.326 --> 01:18.033
- It’s a sign from the devil!
- The end time?

01:18.120 --> 01:20.076
It’s Satan!
God help us!

01:20.164 --> 01:21.870
- We should pray.
- Run!

01:21.958 --> 01:23.368
[ Screams ]

01:23.459 --> 01:24.869
[Crowd Shouting, Screaming ]

01:24.961 --> 01:26.497
Run! Run!

01:37.848 --> 01:39.384
[ Dog Barking In Distance]

01:39.475 --> 01:43.093
[ Booth ]
Okay, day care for you
and a crime scene for us.

01:43.187 --> 01:46.304
Bones, if you don’t hurry up,
people are gonna start messin’
with your remains.

01:46.440 --> 01:48.101
And we don’t want that.
[Christine Cooing ]

01:48.192 --> 01:51.150
Hey,baby,baby.
Da-da. F.B.l.

01:51.237 --> 01:52.852
I don’t know what to wear.

01:52.947 --> 01:55.609
What do you mean?
We’re going to a garbage dump.
There’s no dress code.

01:55.700 --> 01:58.407
Everything I put on,
all the clothes I had
before the baby,

01:58.494 --> 02:00.780
ljust feel like I’m not—

02:00.871 --> 02:02.907
- [ Sighs ]
You know what I mean?
- No, I don’t.

02:02.999 --> 02:04.864
Listen, we gotta get Christine
to the day care.

02:04.959 --> 02:07.291
lfeel like I’m
in someone else’s body.

02:07.378 --> 02:10.541
Oh, no. You are not
in somebody else’s body.

02:10.631 --> 02:13.418
Trust me.
I know your body.

02:13.509 --> 02:15.249
I guarantee that one.

02:15.344 --> 02:18.802
Okay, now you’re humoring me
so that you can get to the crime scene.

02:18.889 --> 02:21.175
Yes, I am. So, why don’t you
wear the green thingy?

02:21.267 --> 02:23.804
What, this? It makes me look
like a golf course.

02:23.894 --> 02:25.850
Bones, what’s the matter?
You’re never like this.

02:25.938 --> 02:28.054
You don’t think I should
care about how I look?

02:29.108 --> 02:30.973
Right. | get it.

02:31.068 --> 02:33.480
You’re an airplane propeller
and I’m about to walk into you,

02:33.571 --> 02:35.277
so I’m gonna take a step back.

02:35.364 --> 02:36.945
I don’t know what that means.

02:37.033 --> 02:40.116
You’re just feeling
a little vulnerable
because you just had a baby.

02:40.202 --> 02:42.989
Are you saying that I resent our daughter?
I love Christine.

02:43.080 --> 02:45.571
No, no, not at all. ljust—

02:47.043 --> 02:49.329
Look, what do you say
we talk about this later?

02:49.462 --> 02:51.373
We really should
get to work.
Okay, fine.

02:51.464 --> 02:53.671
Should I wear this or this?

02:53.758 --> 02:55.544
Uh, you know what?
They’re both gorgeous.

02:55.634 --> 02:57.090
Ugh! You’re no help at all.

02:58.596 --> 02:59.961
Absolutely no help at all.

03:02.433 --> 03:03.923
Did I say
something wrong?

03:04.143 --> 03:05.349
[Chattering ]

03:05.436 --> 03:06.801
That was the first one?

03:06.896 --> 03:09.057
[ Police Rad/0 Chatter]
[ Man ]
Twenty yards.

03:09.148 --> 03:11.104
[Siren Wailing]

03:17.531 --> 03:19.863
Thank you.
You’re welcome.

03:19.950 --> 03:22.327
I should’ve worn
the other top,
but you rushed me.

03:22.411 --> 03:24.697
Well, you know what?
You’re wearing—
Give me that.

03:24.789 --> 03:26.495
It’s raining out, okay?
You’re wearing a jumpsuit.

03:26.582 --> 03:28.994
- No one’s gonna know
what you’re wearing.
- I know what I’m wearing.

03:29.085 --> 03:30.791
[ Booth]
Okay, murder
at the Blue Man Group.

03:30.878 --> 03:33.039
What’s with all the dead blue birds?

03:33.130 --> 03:35.337
They picked the victim apart
and died doing it.

03:35.424 --> 03:38.382
- Where are the rest
of the remains?
- With Hodgins.

03:38.469 --> 03:40.585
I’m gonna put “freaky”
in my report, huh?

03:40.721 --> 03:42.507
Yeah, it went
in mine too.
Hey, hey, hey, hey.

03:42.640 --> 03:46.679
Cam, Cam, do me a favor, okay?
When you get an opening,
tell Bones that she looks good.

03:46.769 --> 03:48.179
Excuse me?

03:48.270 --> 03:51.478
I think she’s feeling a bit unattractive
since having the baby.

03:51.607 --> 03:54.644
But isn’t that yourjob?
No, no, I’m the loved one.
That’s not gonna work.

03:54.735 --> 03:58.068
I need you to do that. Please?
Look, I owe you one.
Come on, huh?

03:58.155 --> 04:00.441
All right? All right!

04:00.574 --> 04:03.441
Just say she looks great.
That’s all.
Okay.

04:03.536 --> 04:06.323
[Hodgins ] Well,
we recovered the remains
from the garbage.

04:06.414 --> 04:08.279
[ Brennan ]
What made the remains blue?

04:08.374 --> 04:10.911
Well, there’s
so many chemicals
in this dump,

04:11.001 --> 04:13.959
it’s gonna take a while
to figure out what
the original solution was.

04:14.046 --> 04:16.537
Matches. Probably some kind
of accelerant.

04:16.632 --> 04:19.715
- So someone tried to torch him.
- That’s a lot harder to do
than people think.

04:19.802 --> 04:21.417
So, the killer’s probably an amateur.

04:21.512 --> 04:23.548
Adolescent Call/phora V/C/ﬂa,

04:23.639 --> 04:26.676
which means that
our blue friend here has
been dead for about two weeks.

04:26.767 --> 04:30.476
Judging by the advanced
fusion of the sacrum,

04:30.563 --> 04:33.100
he was male, around 30 and tall—

04:33.190 --> 04:35.146
approximately
185 centimeters.

04:35.234 --> 04:37.691
Oh, wow. Blue rats too?

04:37.778 --> 04:40.110
Yeah, and raccoons
and squirrels.

04:40.197 --> 04:42.654
And everyone who snacked
on this guy is dead.

04:42.741 --> 04:45.027
Where’s his hair?

04:45.119 --> 04:46.484
He has no hair.

04:46.579 --> 04:49.787
Well, the birds probably took it.
It would make a lovely nest.

04:49.874 --> 04:51.034
[ Mouthing Word ]

04:52.168 --> 04:53.783
Speaking of lovely,

04:53.878 --> 04:57.791
you look particularly
lovely yourself today,
Dr. Brennan.

04:57.882 --> 05:00.715
- Booth told you
to say that, didn’t he?
- What?

05:01.844 --> 05:04.005
Sorry. You’re on your own, Seeley.

05:04.096 --> 05:06.712
What— Cause of death.
How did he die?
Cause of death?

05:08.267 --> 05:09.757
Do I wanna know
what’s goin’ on here?

05:09.852 --> 05:11.888
- No. No, no, no, no.
- Cause of death.

05:11.979 --> 05:14.220
The scavenging has obscured
any other injuries to the bones,

05:14.315 --> 05:16.522
so cause of death will
have to wait till the lab.

05:16.609 --> 05:18.474
Of course. Right.
Of course it does.

05:18.569 --> 05:20.184
But you look good in that.

05:20.279 --> 05:24.192
Somehow you make
that old jumpsuit thing
look very hot.

05:24.283 --> 05:25.989
- Seeley.
- Right.

05:26.076 --> 05:28.328
Let’s get it all back
to the Jeffersonian, huh?

05:28.412 --> 05:30.448
Blue Man Group
and everything.

05:30.539 --> 05:31.915
Here we go.

05:33.667 --> 05:35.203
We—

06:15.459 --> 06:19.043
None of the markings
to the upper body is cause of death.

06:19.129 --> 06:23.372
The straight grooves
with the flat floors are rats.

06:23.467 --> 06:27.301
These are dogs, and those
are from the seagulls.

06:27.388 --> 06:30.004
The scoring to both femurs
could be from an assault.

06:30.099 --> 06:32.932
- No, those are mostly
the result of—
- Coyotes!

06:33.018 --> 06:34.554
Very good. Yes.

06:34.645 --> 06:36.852
Thank you. Thank you very much.

06:38.023 --> 06:40.435
I love my job!

06:41.277 --> 06:43.063
Okay.
[ Chuckles ]

06:43.153 --> 06:44.859
Can’t wait to start
the facial reconstruction,

06:44.947 --> 06:47.108
see if anybody reported
a blue man missing.

06:47.199 --> 06:49.190
Krishna has been depicted
as having blue skin,

06:49.285 --> 06:54.655
but he died in 3102 B.C.E.,
so decomposition would be
a little more advanced.

06:54.748 --> 06:56.329
[ Loud Laughing]

06:58.419 --> 07:01.456
Wow, you are madly in love
with yourjob.

07:01.547 --> 07:03.208
Any closer to what
that blue stuff is?

07:03.299 --> 07:06.291
So far, I found dimethyl benzyl,
ammonium chloride,

07:06.385 --> 07:08.421
sodium nitrite and lactic acid.

07:08.512 --> 07:10.719
But those could’ve been present
in the dump before the body arrived.

07:10.806 --> 07:12.467
- That’s a no, right?
- I’ll get it—

07:12.558 --> 07:14.924
after I finish blending together
the remaining tissue.

07:15.019 --> 07:18.511
Hey, if anybody needs me,
I’ll be in my office, gagging.

07:18.606 --> 07:21.723
We won’t be able to use
the bones to identify assault...

07:21.817 --> 07:25.275
until we rule out all the damage
caused by scavengers.

07:25.362 --> 07:28.104
- He might have been poisoned.
- I’ll know after the tox screen.

07:28.198 --> 07:30.689
If you can find
an uncompromised
piece of flesh.

07:30.784 --> 07:33.992
Oh, you bone guys
are unimaginative.

07:35.539 --> 07:38.155
We have—
[Arastoo ]
The tongue!

07:38.250 --> 07:41.287
lt would’ve been protected
from contamination.

07:41.378 --> 07:43.460
Would you like
to do the honors,
Mr. Vaziri?

07:43.547 --> 07:45.208
Thank you.

07:52.222 --> 07:56.716
[ Sighs ]
Truly, madly, deeply in love.

08:02.441 --> 08:04.477
The dump could represent
a funeral pyre.

08:04.610 --> 08:05.941
A what?
A pyre.

08:06.028 --> 08:07.313
He was doused in blue liquid...

08:07.404 --> 08:08.735
that was supposed to cremate him.

08:08.822 --> 08:10.483
I’m thinking
it could be some kind
of a ritualized murder.

08:10.574 --> 08:11.780
That’s crazy. You’re supposed...

08:11.867 --> 08:13.073
to be the best profiler we have.

08:13.160 --> 08:14.149
l was just spitballing.

08:14.244 --> 08:15.324
You’re reaching.
That’s what you’re doing.

08:15.412 --> 08:16.572
You’re reaching, all right?

08:16.664 --> 08:18.950
Bodies are dumped in landfills
all the time, Sweets.

08:19.083 --> 08:21.995
Something else goin’ on?
Nope, nothing else
is going on.

08:22.086 --> 08:24.327
l have everything under control.

08:24.421 --> 08:25.797
If nothing is going on,

08:25.881 --> 08:27.417
uh, what do you have
under control?

08:27.508 --> 08:29.294
You think you’re smart, don’t you?

08:29.385 --> 08:31.046
Oh, I know I am. Top of my class.

08:31.136 --> 08:32.637
Honor society in graduate school.

08:32.721 --> 08:34.052
Youngest psychologist ever to—

08:34.139 --> 08:36.300
Let’s just focus on the case.
Concentrate on the case at hand.

08:36.392 --> 08:38.178
I think maybe you’re afraid of something.

08:38.268 --> 08:40.350
I’m afraid of what I’m gonna do
to you if you don’t shut up.

08:40.437 --> 08:42.177
I think you’re feeling
marginalized because...

08:42.272 --> 08:44.763
the baby is taking Dr. Brennan’s
attention away from you.

08:44.858 --> 08:47.019
What? I’m sorry. What’d you say?

08:47.111 --> 08:50.103
[Cell Phone Ringing]
What?

08:50.989 --> 08:53.605
Whoa. Easy bi
You okay? 9 guy.

08:54.785 --> 08:56.241
Yeah, I’m fine.
What is it?

08:56.328 --> 08:58.489
I got a hit on
my facial reconstruction.

08:58.580 --> 09:00.707
His name is Santiago Valmont,

09:00.791 --> 09:04.534
and he’s a hair stylist
at a high-end salon
in Georgetown.

09:04.628 --> 09:08.337
- I sent you the file.
- All right. Hold on here.

09:08.424 --> 09:12.633
Three female clients
reported him missing,
none of them family.

09:12.720 --> 09:16.212
Yeah. A good-looking hairdresser
with three women who miss him?

09:16.306 --> 09:19.173
I’d say he was giving
his clients more than a blowout.

09:23.147 --> 09:25.889
Dude, is that a cart full of critters?

09:25.983 --> 09:28.565
Dr. Brennan
wants me to rule out
all the scavenger marks...

09:28.652 --> 09:30.438
so we can identify injuries
that might indicate assault.

09:30.529 --> 09:34.147
So I went back to the dump
and collected them
so I could match dentition.

09:34.241 --> 09:36.402
Are you bucking for teacher’s pet
or something?

09:36.493 --> 09:38.233
Because Dr. B.
doesn’t really do that.

09:38.328 --> 09:39.943
I set a certain standard of excellence,

09:40.038 --> 09:41.414
and I don’t want to disappoint myself.

09:41.498 --> 09:44.615
- Okay.
- What’s that?

09:44.710 --> 09:47.543
| pureed some of the flesh
to ID. what he was doused in.

09:47.629 --> 09:50.086
l have total faith in your
ability to resolve the mystery,

09:50.174 --> 09:52.005
because, dude, you rock.

09:52.092 --> 09:54.469
Okay, what is going on?

09:54.553 --> 09:56.509
Have you been huffing this stuff
or something?

10:00.350 --> 10:03.137
No one is supposed to see this yet.
You can’t tell anyone.

10:03.228 --> 10:06.095
It’s the galleys from the Journal
of Forensic Anthropology.

10:06.190 --> 10:07.896
Five up from the bottom.

10:07.983 --> 10:11.350
“New Methodologies
for Osteometric Analysis
in Human Remains”...

10:11.445 --> 10:13.060
by Arastoo Vaziri.

10:13.197 --> 10:16.360
Hey, man, congratulations!
Thanks.

10:16.450 --> 10:20.068
I’ve just been so pumped,
and I can’t say anything
until the Journal comes out.

10:20.204 --> 10:23.241
Check out page 41.
Forty-one.

10:24.541 --> 10:26.122
You gave me a footnote.

10:26.251 --> 10:29.209
You deserve it.
Well, thank you.

10:29.296 --> 10:31.958
Wow. Now, let me give you
a little piece of advice.

10:32.049 --> 10:34.040
You’ve been published.
Excellent.

10:34.134 --> 10:36.671
Nowjust, you know,
relax and enjoy it.

10:36.762 --> 10:39.469
That’s not how it works.
I gotta figure out my next project.

10:39.556 --> 10:41.387
Academia’s a bitch, bro.

10:48.232 --> 10:51.269
When was the last time
any of you saw Santiago?
[Woman ] Two weeks ago.

10:51.360 --> 10:54.318
My husband has been in St. Louis
for two months.

10:54.404 --> 10:58.022
A woman needs to be
appreciated occasionally.

10:58.116 --> 11:00.277
After cutting up oranges
for soccer practice,

11:00.369 --> 11:03.281
there was nothing like
getting blown out by Santiago.

11:04.248 --> 11:05.533
[Murmurs]

11:05.624 --> 11:09.116
Huh. Uh, so you were—
you were all then,

11:09.211 --> 11:12.669
uh, appreciated by Mr. Valmont?

11:12.756 --> 11:14.997
- And none of you were jealous?
- We each had our own
appointments.

11:15.092 --> 11:17.879
I had him every Wednesday
and Friday at 5:00.

11:17.970 --> 11:19.961
l was Thursdays at 1:00...

11:20.055 --> 11:22.262
before picking up the kids
for soccer practice.

11:22.349 --> 11:26.183
You know, it’s very rare not to
feel proprietary when involved
in an intimate relationship.

11:26.270 --> 11:27.976
Well, someone was jealous.

11:28.063 --> 11:29.678
His Saturday appointment.

11:29.773 --> 11:31.229
Bitch always demanded the 6:00.

11:31.316 --> 11:32.852
Why would that matter?

11:32.943 --> 11:34.854
It’s the last appointment
of the day.

11:34.987 --> 11:37.854
There’s no rush.
It’s good planning.
Uh-huh.

11:37.948 --> 11:40.439
But Santiago started complaining
about her last month.

11:40.534 --> 11:43.241
Said she was getting
crazy and jealous.

11:43.328 --> 11:46.286
- Did he mention a name?
- No, he respected our privacy.

11:46.373 --> 11:50.207
We respected his.
Right, girls?

11:50.294 --> 11:52.455
Mm-hmm.

11:56.508 --> 12:00.296
I can’t believe he’s dead.
He was my best stylist.

12:00.387 --> 12:02.628
My first hire
when I opened the place.

12:02.723 --> 12:05.055
Well, he had a regular client
on Saturdays at 6:00.

12:05.142 --> 12:06.757
We need to know
who that was.

12:06.852 --> 12:09.844
l have no idea.
He booked his own appointments.

12:09.938 --> 12:12.145
He wanted to keep
his clients confidential.

12:12.232 --> 12:13.813
Because he was
having sex with them?

12:13.901 --> 12:15.983
Did you know about that?

12:16.069 --> 12:20.483
Look, if you wanna know
about Santiago’s clients,
ask Theo, his shampoo boy.

12:20.574 --> 12:23.532
He’s over at Santiago’s station.

12:23.619 --> 12:25.109
l have a salon to run.

12:25.203 --> 12:27.535
Of course you do.

12:27.623 --> 12:29.784
Shampoo boy, huh?

12:29.875 --> 12:31.706
[Woman ]
We’re gonna wash your hair.

12:31.793 --> 12:33.499
Excuse me. Hey. F.B.l.

12:33.587 --> 12:35.953
I need to ask you some questions
about Santiago.

12:36.048 --> 12:38.710
Oh, God.
Something’s wrong, isn’t it?

12:38.800 --> 12:40.415
Santiago’s not playing hooky.

12:40.510 --> 12:43.673
He’s dead, Theo.
Santiago was murdered.

12:45.015 --> 12:47.973
No, that-that— that can’t be.

12:49.645 --> 12:51.385
- Kevin.
- Who?

12:51.480 --> 12:55.644
Kevin has been
trying to get his station
for the past two years.

12:55.734 --> 12:58.726
-Think he’d kill for that chair?
-You people have something
you want to say to me?

12:58.820 --> 13:01.277
Santiago’s been murdered.

13:01.365 --> 13:04.857
Well, if there is any justice,
it was that poor girl he made
look like a skunk.

13:04.952 --> 13:06.533
Let’s just focus.

13:06.620 --> 13:09.327
We’re looking for a client
who had Santiago’s 6:00
appointment on Saturday.

13:09.414 --> 13:13.657
I leave at 5:00 on Saturdays,
so, if he had a private client,
I wouldn’t know.

13:13.752 --> 13:15.868
Oh, please!

13:16.880 --> 13:18.996
Hey, what are you doing?

13:19.091 --> 13:21.082
Hey, that’s his private—

13:23.595 --> 13:25.210
Now you don’t need a warrant.

13:27.057 --> 13:28.968
You’re welcome, G-man.

13:31.853 --> 13:34.936
Look at this, huh?
A tip envelope.

13:35.023 --> 13:39.107
“You’re mine, darlin’.
Don’t forget it. XOXO. Ruby.”

13:39.194 --> 13:41.560
Maybe he didn’t live up
to his side of the bargain.

13:52.582 --> 13:54.789
Santiago was my stylist,
and I gave him a tip.

13:54.876 --> 13:56.412
I don’t see what the big deal is.

13:56.503 --> 13:59.916
My dad was a barber.
The biggest tip he ever got
was a glazed ham, okay?

14:00.007 --> 14:02.589
He got a thousand dollars.
That’s gotta mean something.

14:02.676 --> 14:04.712
He was a really,
really good stylist.

14:04.803 --> 14:06.339
Ruby, we know
all about Santiago.

14:06.430 --> 14:08.921
We know
that he was sleeping
with his clients.

14:11.518 --> 14:13.600
l was more than just a client.
I loved him.

14:13.687 --> 14:15.177
He knew that.

14:15.272 --> 14:17.058
You loved him? Right.

14:17.149 --> 14:20.767
So I’m sure the idea
of him sharing other women
really bothered you, huh?

14:20.861 --> 14:23.523
But I would never
do anything to hurt him.

14:23.613 --> 14:25.820
I gave him the money
to help him.

14:25.907 --> 14:28.819
He had debts from—

14:28.910 --> 14:30.616
from buying drugs.

14:30.704 --> 14:33.446
It’s the only reason
why he was messing around
with those skanks—

14:33.582 --> 14:35.368
’cause he was high.
What kind of drugs?

14:35.459 --> 14:38.417
Weed, pills, some cocaine
every now and then.

14:38.545 --> 14:42.037
Okay, so you made sure
he was supplied?
No! God, no!

14:42.132 --> 14:45.795
l was trying to get him into
treatment, but he wanted to
get his dealer off his back.

14:46.803 --> 14:50.295
l was trying to save him,
not kill him.

14:58.940 --> 15:01.602
The stuff is blue,
and he was a hairdresser.

15:01.693 --> 15:03.854
So, it’s gotta be Barbicide.

15:03.987 --> 15:05.898
And Barbicide
is flammable, right?
Yes.

15:05.989 --> 15:08.856
But it doesn’t contain
meta-diaminotoluene.

15:08.950 --> 15:12.078
Okay, so, if the blue stuff degraded,
we’ll never know what it was?

15:12.162 --> 15:15.825
Well, maybe, if you were dealing
with an average scientist.

15:15.916 --> 15:19.829
I, however, have discovered
that the color component here,
it didn’t degrade.

15:19.920 --> 15:22.411
It’s an unusual formulation
of copper salts...

15:22.506 --> 15:26.920
frequently used to clean
and disinfect pools
and-and fountains.

15:27.010 --> 15:29.843
Yeah, but he wasn’t
found anywhere near
a pool or a fountain.

15:29.930 --> 15:32.216
I know. That’s the problem.

15:36.686 --> 15:38.642
Ah, Miss Montenegro,
there you are.

15:38.730 --> 15:41.722
Oh, Arastoo.
Congratulations!

15:41.817 --> 15:44.229
- You weren’t supposed
to tell anyone.
- I didn’t.

15:46.279 --> 15:48.565
Well, she’s my wife,
so that doesn’t count.

15:48.657 --> 15:49.988
Where—
Where is that written?

15:50.075 --> 15:53.238
- It’s common knowledge.
- Oh. Okay then.

15:53.328 --> 15:55.239
Thank you.
But don’t tell anyone else.

15:55.330 --> 15:57.241
I might have an idea
for my next paper.

15:57.332 --> 16:00.699
“New Insights
into Forensic Odontology.”
Pretty exciting, huh?

16:00.794 --> 16:03.376
Yeah, yeah.
Let me catch my breath.

16:03.463 --> 16:06.421
I’m taking Mikrosil molds
of the scavengers’ teeth.

16:06.508 --> 16:08.544
| theorize that if
we can scan the bones,

16:08.635 --> 16:11.718
then input the exact dentition
of each scavenger,

16:11.805 --> 16:15.172
we should be able to use
the Angelatron to strip away
their teeth marks,

16:15.267 --> 16:17.929
leaving only those injuries
that might point to an assault.

16:18.019 --> 16:19.395
That’s interesting.

16:20.605 --> 16:23.472
It’s a little crazy,
but it’s interesting.

16:23.567 --> 16:25.649
- So you’ll help?
- Yeah.

16:25.735 --> 16:28.647
As long as I don’t have
to touch those things.

16:34.661 --> 16:36.162
Thanks, Cam.

16:36.246 --> 16:39.158
So, Cam’s tox screen confirms
that Santiago had drugs in his system.

16:39.249 --> 16:41.535
All right.
So, Saturday at 6:00
was telling the truth.

16:41.668 --> 16:44.535
Looks like it.
So why are we heading
to, uh, Little India?

16:44.629 --> 16:47.746
Santiago’s last credit card charge
was for a parking meter there...

16:47.841 --> 16:50.674
in front of an import store
that was busted for drugs last year.

16:50.760 --> 16:52.796
Okay, hold on.
Shouldn’t you have just taken a right?

16:52.888 --> 16:55.630
Oh, no.
My car’s got the Entune system.

16:55.724 --> 16:57.885
Finds the best route, least traffic.

16:57.976 --> 16:59.512
So, we’re driving in a robot?

16:59.603 --> 17:01.343
Yes, my robot friend, Camry.

17:01.438 --> 17:03.178
He calls me Dave.

17:03.273 --> 17:05.559
That— That is incredibly geeky of you.

17:05.650 --> 17:08.733
- You got the reference,
so what does that mean?
- Whoa. Look at that.

17:08.862 --> 17:11.399
You get sports scores
on this thing too?
Uh-huh.

17:11.489 --> 17:14.151
I slept in here one night
after Daisy and I had a fight...

17:14.242 --> 17:16.699
and hated to leave
when we made up.

17:16.786 --> 17:19.448
So, how— how are things
with you and Dr. Brennan?

17:19.581 --> 17:21.242
Fine. Absolutely fine.
Yeah?

17:21.333 --> 17:23.790
I’m not sleeping in my car if that’s
what you’re trying to get at.

17:23.877 --> 17:27.836
Ooh. It’s quite common
to experience a lull in
sexual activity after a baby.

17:27.923 --> 17:29.003
Stop.

17:29.799 --> 17:31.710
Okay.
Stop. Okay?

17:31.801 --> 17:34.008
We’re fine. Everything’s great.

17:34.137 --> 17:35.752
We’re better than fine.
Mmm.

17:35.847 --> 17:38.634
| just want you to know
that I’m here if you need me
for anything.

17:40.936 --> 17:42.972
Not— Okay, not anything.

17:43.063 --> 17:44.769
|-| wasn’t referring to—

17:44.856 --> 17:46.642
My last statement
wasn’t tied to my—

17:46.733 --> 17:49.019
You know what?
You’re just gonna let me
keep going, aren’t you?

17:49.110 --> 17:52.398
Absolutely. Hopefully,
your little robot car here
will be able to bail you out.

17:52.489 --> 17:54.150
[Sighs]

17:54.241 --> 17:55.822
No, it doesn’t do that.

17:59.329 --> 18:01.115
This was Mr. Vaziri’s idea?

18:01.206 --> 18:05.199
Yeah. This is a digital scan
of Santiago’s skeleton.

18:05.293 --> 18:08.080
And the smaller windows
show the dentition...

18:08.171 --> 18:09.786
from the scavengers
that Arastoo gathered.

18:09.881 --> 18:13.169
So this allows you to remove
all the postmortem trauma?

18:13.301 --> 18:16.668
Ingenious.
If it works.

18:21.184 --> 18:24.176
How did you feel
after you had Michael?

18:25.438 --> 18:28.145
I’m guessing you don’t mean
the joy and happiness...

18:28.233 --> 18:29.894
and ovenNhelming love.

18:29.985 --> 18:32.818
No, that part I like very much.

18:33.863 --> 18:36.605
Oh. Your old clothes don’t fit, right?

18:36.700 --> 18:39.692
Oh, God. I can’t get comfortable
in anything.

18:39.786 --> 18:42.277
Booth doesn’t understand.
He tries, but—

18:42.372 --> 18:43.908
Men cannot understand.

18:43.999 --> 18:45.990
lt scares them
when we talk about clothing.

18:46.084 --> 18:50.293
You should buy yourself
some new clothes and-and
give yourself a spa day.

18:50.380 --> 18:53.167
Well, l-l’m too busy.
We don’t even have
cause of death yet.

18:53.258 --> 18:55.624
Wait a minute.
You just grew a human.

18:55.719 --> 18:57.960
Someone should be
throwing you a parade.

18:58.054 --> 19:00.591
Getting some new clothes
and a facial, I mean—

19:00.682 --> 19:02.297
that seems like
the least you deserve.

19:02.392 --> 19:03.928
How’s it goin’?

19:04.019 --> 19:06.055
Congratulations, Mr. Vaziri.

19:06.146 --> 19:08.011
Oh. Thank you.

19:08.106 --> 19:09.721
Y-You weren’t supposed to know.

19:09.858 --> 19:12.099
[ Beeping ]
Why would you
keep this from me?

19:12.193 --> 19:15.606
Oh, this. I thought you meant
my article in the Journal
of Forensic Anthropology.

19:15.697 --> 19:17.358
No one is supposed
to know about that.

19:17.449 --> 19:19.690
Then why did you just tell me?

19:20.869 --> 19:22.450
Right.

19:22.537 --> 19:25.870
So, you like what I did here?
l was thinking it could be another paper.

19:25.957 --> 19:28.790
Yeah, it’s actually working out
better than I thought.

19:28.877 --> 19:32.119
Here. Look at these marks.
These weren’t made by animals.

19:32.213 --> 19:33.464
Can you enhance them?

19:39.304 --> 19:40.919
Oh, this is awesome.

19:41.014 --> 19:43.005
No, it is merely helpful.

19:43.099 --> 19:46.762
Do not discount
what you can learn from touch
and careful observation.

19:46.853 --> 19:49.720
- So, this is cause of death?
- No.

19:49.814 --> 19:52.851
These marks aren’t deep enough
or close enough to any of the
arteries that could be severed.

19:52.942 --> 19:54.398
Perhaps not,

19:54.486 --> 19:58.229
but the linear cut marks
on the side of the cranium
tell us a lot,

19:58.323 --> 20:00.188
don’t they, Mr. Vaziri?

20:00.283 --> 20:02.069
- They do?
- Yes.

20:02.160 --> 20:05.448
There are micro-incisions
here and here.

20:05.538 --> 20:08.120
That’s why the victim’s
hair was missing.

20:09.501 --> 20:10.991
He was scalped.

20:17.050 --> 20:19.712
,/‘,r [ Background: lno’ian Pop]

20:21.429 --> 20:24.967
Like I said, Sweets, the owner
was arrested for selling drugs
last year, okay?

20:25.058 --> 20:27.720
So Santiago
could’ve been killed
in a drug deal gone bad.

20:27.811 --> 20:31.053
Well, I never heard
of a drug dealer
scalping anyone, huh?

20:31.147 --> 20:34.639
A ritualistic killing
doesn’t seem so odd now,
does it?

20:34.776 --> 20:36.892
Ooh!
Hey. What’s goin’ down,
good people?

20:36.986 --> 20:39.147
