on your rights, Poorab,

27:39.534 --> 27:41.695
maybe you can tell me why
you ran off with a bag...

27:41.786 --> 27:44.653
that contained hair
from over 25 corpses?

27:44.747 --> 27:46.703
What?
Yeah. According
to our lab,

27:46.791 --> 27:49.703
your client here killed and scalped
over 25 people for their hair.

27:49.794 --> 27:51.330
That’s just sick.

27:51.420 --> 27:54.082
No, man, no, no.
That is whack, man.
I didn’t kill anyone, man.

27:54.215 --> 27:56.831
| hustled the hair
from my uncle’s mortuary.
What?

27:56.926 --> 27:59.292
Look, every Wednesday,
I sneak in there,

27:59.387 --> 28:02.254
I cut the hair off the stiffs
before they stick them
in the furnace.

28:02.348 --> 28:05.135
I sell them to beauty shops
for extensions.

28:05.226 --> 28:06.716
Wait a second. Extensions?

28:06.811 --> 28:09.302
But the customers didn’t know
it came from dead people.

28:09.397 --> 28:11.888
Santiago Valmont came to you
to pick up hair?

28:11.983 --> 28:14.065
That’s all! l was his supplier.

28:14.151 --> 28:17.109
All right, him and his boy
at the salon— um, Kevin.

28:17.196 --> 28:20.313
- Kevin.
- Yeah. Chicks pay big bucks
for weaves of that stuff.

28:20.408 --> 28:22.569
You got one, right?
I bet it’s one of mine.

28:22.660 --> 28:25.572
I can’t do this!
You’re— You’re an animal.

28:25.663 --> 28:27.324
I hate law!

28:27.415 --> 28:29.406
l’m— I’m going
to shave my head.

28:29.500 --> 28:31.286
You forgot your, uh—

28:32.837 --> 28:34.623
Right. So you supplied Kevin too?

28:35.673 --> 28:38.506
I’d like to wait
till I get another lawyer.

28:38.593 --> 28:40.458
You-You understand?

28:48.978 --> 28:51.936
Okay. We’ve got an hour
before the sitter takes off,

28:52.023 --> 28:54.514
so if we leave right now,
we can go crazy...

28:54.609 --> 28:57.396
and treat ourselves with
a trip to the dry cleaners.

28:57.486 --> 28:59.226
Mmm. As exciting as that sounds,

28:59.322 --> 29:01.859
I can’t go anywhere
until I figure out
what this blue stuff is.

29:01.991 --> 29:05.529
This stuff is incredibly acidic.
Not to mention boring.

29:05.620 --> 29:07.656
Come on, honey.
Let’s go.

29:07.747 --> 29:12.366
If we leave right now,
we can fool around in the car
before we get home.

29:12.460 --> 29:16.078
- Sounds good, right?
- Mmm. Actually,
that does sound fun.

29:16.213 --> 29:17.248
[ Chuckles ]
Yeah.
Yeah?

29:17.340 --> 29:20.628
Oh, my God! That— That’s it.

29:20.718 --> 29:23.425
This is an extremely
flammable poison...

29:23.512 --> 29:25.548
that contains both sodium silicate
and glycolic acid,

29:25.640 --> 29:27.756
which is basically
degraded ethylene glycol.

29:27.850 --> 29:29.306
It’s antifreeze!

29:29.435 --> 29:31.767
He was doused
in antifreeze?
Yes!

29:31.854 --> 29:33.810
That is it.

29:33.898 --> 29:37.015
I did it, Ange.
I figured it out.

29:37.109 --> 29:40.442
Now I’m really feeling like
foolin’ around in that car.

29:46.327 --> 29:47.942
Here.
Okay.

29:48.037 --> 29:51.154
Oh, it is not a good time
unless you know your way around
a Brazilian Blowout.

29:51.248 --> 29:53.284
We are seriously
understaffed right now.

29:53.376 --> 29:55.708
I’m sure Booth could help.
His father was a barber.

29:55.795 --> 29:59.788
Right. If she doesn’t learn
how to properly layer, you’re
gonna lose a lot of business.

30:01.050 --> 30:03.291
- Where’s Kevin?
- I don’t know.

30:03.386 --> 30:05.843
He disappeared,
and he took everything with him.

30:05.930 --> 30:07.136
His station was cleaned out.

30:07.223 --> 30:09.259
For five years
he’s been working here,

30:09.350 --> 30:12.262
and then he takes off
without even a phone call.

30:13.771 --> 30:16.433
Wait. You guys don’t think that—

30:17.400 --> 30:18.856
- Oh.
- Oh.

30:18.943 --> 30:20.353
Oh.

30:26.742 --> 30:30.860
Mr. Vaziri, have you found
anything yet that might point
to a cause of death?

30:33.082 --> 30:34.947
Excuse me?
Cause of death.

30:35.042 --> 30:36.657
That’s the reason we’re here.

30:36.752 --> 30:38.663
Yes, I know. I’m sorry.
I got distracted.

30:38.754 --> 30:43.043
Uh, I noted various scrapes
and anomalies, but none seem
to be related to his murder.

30:43.134 --> 30:45.375
Why are you distracted?
Do I need to get
another intern?

30:45.469 --> 30:47.551
No. No. It’s just—

30:47.638 --> 30:50.926
I got word that the journal
isn’t going to publish my paper.

30:51.017 --> 30:52.723
Is that all?

30:52.810 --> 30:57.224
It got pulled in favor of
a puff piece about Selena Gomez
on a fossil hunt.

30:57.314 --> 31:01.182
I’m not familiar with
Dr. Gomez’s work, but I look
fonNard to reading about it.

31:01.277 --> 31:03.689
I worked on that paper
for six months.

31:03.779 --> 31:06.270
- It was excellent.
- Yes, I know.

31:07.324 --> 31:09.451
They sent it to me for review.

31:09.535 --> 31:11.992
You aren’t supposed to know
who’s on the review board,

31:12.079 --> 31:13.990
but since they’re not
publishing it.

31:14.081 --> 31:15.787
You thought it was excellent?

31:15.875 --> 31:18.958
Yes, although I haven’t reviewed
Dr. Gomez’s findings.

31:19.045 --> 31:21.161
Thank you.
Thank you very much.

31:21.255 --> 31:24.873
You’re welcome.
However, I am quite pleased
you won’t be published.

31:24.967 --> 31:26.832
I-I don’t understand.

31:26.927 --> 31:31.216
You are clearly
too immature to understand
what being published means.

31:31.307 --> 31:33.468
I know many scientists
who were published...

31:33.559 --> 31:37.051
who are useless and forgotten today...

31:37.146 --> 31:39.478
because they thought
what they do wasn’t as important...

31:39.565 --> 31:41.681
as who they were perceived to be.

31:41.776 --> 31:44.017
Do yourjob, Mr. Vaziri.

31:44.111 --> 31:49.071
You possess many more
impressively calibrated sensory
organs than any computer.

31:49.158 --> 31:51.149
Touch the bones.

31:51.243 --> 31:53.575
Let them give you the answers.

31:53.662 --> 31:56.369
That’s why you’re here.

31:58.876 --> 32:01.709
Good luck. I hope
I don’t have to fire you.

32:07.093 --> 32:09.049
[ Sweets ]
You worked at that salon
for five years...

32:09.136 --> 32:11.343
and you just walked out
without a word to anybody?

32:11.430 --> 32:15.264
You think l was the only one
that hated Santiago?

32:15.351 --> 32:19.094
Talk to the other stylists,
to his shampoo boy, to Tabitha.

32:19.188 --> 32:23.101
For God’s sake,
the man was a prima donna
with no talent.

32:23.192 --> 32:25.558
Besides,
I was busier than he was,

32:25.653 --> 32:27.985
so why would I have
to kill him for his chair?

32:28.072 --> 32:30.939
Maybe, but you
may have killed him because
you were his drug dealer.

32:31.033 --> 32:33.024
- No comment.
- No comment. Great.

32:33.119 --> 32:35.280
Our team already
checked your apartment.
We found your stash.

32:35.371 --> 32:38.989
Third ceiling tile from
the Kathy Griffin poster,
in case you don’t believe us.

32:39.083 --> 32:42.667
It’s only a matter of time
till we match them to the drugs
found in Santiago’s system.

32:42.753 --> 32:48.043
Okay. So, I may have
sold Santiago a few
recreational aids. Big deal.

32:48.134 --> 32:50.295
We know that he owed you
a thousand dollars.

32:50.386 --> 32:52.172
You got mad
because he didn’t pay.

32:52.263 --> 32:55.596
[ Chuckles ]
You really think that I would
get myself dirty with his blood?

32:55.683 --> 32:59.096
- Do you see what I wear?
- Why were you heading for
the airport then, Kevin?

32:59.186 --> 33:01.472
Last time I checked,
dealing drugs was illegal.

33:01.564 --> 33:03.145
- True. Very, very true.
- Yeah.

33:03.232 --> 33:05.518
That’s a shame, though,
that your car did overheat.

33:05.609 --> 33:07.645
Yeah. And you know
what’s weird about that?

33:07.736 --> 33:09.601
According to your
credit card records,

33:09.697 --> 33:12.109
you bought two gallons
of antifreeze just last week,

33:12.199 --> 33:14.406
but we didn’t find any
in your car, so—

33:15.077 --> 33:16.317
So?

33:16.412 --> 33:18.994
So, Santiago’s killer
doused him with antifreeze...

33:19.081 --> 33:21.413
and tried to light him
on fire.

33:23.127 --> 33:24.537
Oh, God.

33:26.005 --> 33:28.337
Well, I mean—

33:28.424 --> 33:31.086
Well, somebody must have
stolen it from my trunk.

33:31.177 --> 33:32.792
I mean, there’s
no other explanation.

33:32.887 --> 33:35.094
Really? ’Cause I could
think of a few more.

33:42.855 --> 33:45.221
I shouldn’t have left
Mr. Vaziri alone.

33:45.316 --> 33:47.307
He hasn’t been doing
his best work lately.

33:47.401 --> 33:49.767
Oh, he’ll be fine.

33:49.862 --> 33:52.604
Besides, I had to kill people
to get a reservation here.

33:52.698 --> 33:57.692
ljust feel like
my time would’ve been
better spent at the lab.

33:57.786 --> 33:59.196
[ Moans]
No.

33:59.288 --> 34:01.904
No, you are doing
the right thing, honey.

34:01.999 --> 34:03.785
And not just
for yourself either.

34:03.876 --> 34:06.583
Arastoo needs time alone
with those bones...

34:06.670 --> 34:10.162
just as much
as you need to be here.

34:10.257 --> 34:12.293
[ Moaning]

34:12.384 --> 34:14.090
Mmm. This is—
[ Chuckles ]

34:14.178 --> 34:16.089
This is very pleasant.

34:16.180 --> 34:18.011
Oh, just like that.
That’s great.

34:18.098 --> 34:20.430
Hey, do you wanna go
clothes shopping later?

34:20.517 --> 34:22.018
Oh, absolutely.

34:22.102 --> 34:27.267
You know that
the ancient Egyptians
used self—adornment to—

34:27.358 --> 34:30.065
Who cares about
the Egyptians?

34:30.152 --> 34:33.736
[Sighs, Chuckles]
This feels wonderful.

34:33.822 --> 34:34.982
Mmm.

34:35.658 --> 34:37.819
-Mmm.
-Mmm.

34:37.910 --> 34:39.366
Oh.

34:39.453 --> 34:41.193
Mmm.
[Chuckles]

34:41.288 --> 34:43.665
Oh, God.

34:45.000 --> 34:48.618
[Cell Phone Rings]
Oh. Please don’t
answer that.

34:48.712 --> 34:51.920
We are five seconds
away from bliss.

34:52.007 --> 34:56.250
Five, four, three—

34:56.345 --> 34:57.835
Brennan.

34:57.930 --> 35:01.923
[ Sighs ]
I found a superficial incision
at the inferior margin...

35:02.017 --> 35:04.633
on the anterior aspect
of the body of the hyoid.

35:05.771 --> 35:08.854
Where exactly on the hyoid,
Mr. Vaziri?

35:08.941 --> 35:12.308
Two millimeters superior
to the attachment
of the sterno-hyoid.

35:12.444 --> 35:14.605
Are you sure?
It was too small
for the Medio Cam,

35:14.697 --> 35:16.608
but I felt it, just as you said.

35:16.699 --> 35:20.283
The damage was from a blade.
I’m working with Dr. Hodgins
to determine what kind.

35:20.369 --> 35:24.533
How could someone slice
the underside of the hyoid
during a struggle?

35:24.623 --> 35:29.617
Sweetie, get off the phone
and join me in heaven.

35:29.712 --> 35:31.202
[Sighs]

35:32.548 --> 35:34.880
-Mmm.
- I know what happened.

35:34.967 --> 35:37.458
- [ Phone Beeps]
- You were right.
This was an excellent idea.

35:37.553 --> 35:40.295
We should do it more often.

35:40.389 --> 35:42.050
[Chuckles]

35:43.475 --> 35:45.636
Okay.

35:45.728 --> 35:50.222
Hey, I paid my money,
so take me to heaven.

35:57.906 --> 36:00.568
There’s only one way
for the hyoid to be sliced like that.

36:00.659 --> 36:03.321
All right, Bones.
You could’ve changed,
gotten the mask off your face.

36:03.412 --> 36:06.119
Well, I’m finally comfortable.
Are you still dissatisfied
with the way I look?

36:06.206 --> 36:08.822
Huh? Me? Why is this
all of a sudden
about me here?

36:08.959 --> 36:11.541
Kevin was going to
cut Santiago’s hair.
Right.

36:11.628 --> 36:16.167
So he had him sit
in the shampoo chair
with his head all the way back.

36:16.258 --> 36:19.591
That way, a cut
across the throat would
have nicked the hyoid...

36:19.678 --> 36:21.885
and sliced the external
carotid artery.

36:22.014 --> 36:24.881
We should find evidence
of blood.
Mm-mmm.

36:24.975 --> 36:27.512
You’re not— You’re not
gonna find the blood there
’cause Kevin didn’t do it.

36:27.603 --> 36:29.844
But Kevin had motive,
the antifreeze.

36:29.938 --> 36:31.599
He ran. And forensically—

36:31.690 --> 36:33.601
Bones, just trust
the barber’s son, okay?

36:33.692 --> 36:35.683
Santiago, he hated Kevin.
Plus he was vain.

36:35.778 --> 36:37.609
He would never allow him
to work on his hair.

36:37.696 --> 36:40.688
There’s only one person here
who he would trust, okay?

36:40.783 --> 36:42.614
Follow me.
[Hair Dryer Blowing]

36:43.452 --> 36:45.363
Hey, Theo.
That’s nice work.

36:45.454 --> 36:47.035
Oh, thank you.

36:47.122 --> 36:49.579
Tabitha’s giving me a chance
now that there’s an opening.

36:49.666 --> 36:52.578
Please don’t bother him.
He’s working on a customer.

36:52.669 --> 36:55.285
Okay, Bones.
Use your magic wand over here
and see what you get, huh?

36:55.381 --> 36:57.622
This area.

36:57.716 --> 37:01.504
- There’s no blood in the sink.
- Blood?

37:01.595 --> 37:04.553
So, these here are
the extensions that Santiago’s
famous for, right?

37:04.640 --> 37:07.347
- He was a genius.
- But you’re the one
who styled them.

37:07.434 --> 37:10.301
Isn’t that right, Theo?
You’re using the same texturing
technique right now on her.

37:10.396 --> 37:11.977
Isn’t that correct?

37:12.064 --> 37:16.728
The same technique you used
on Santiago when he asked you
to cut his hair.

37:16.819 --> 37:17.979
It’s nice work, by the way.

37:18.112 --> 37:20.478
You got it all wrong.
[ Brennan ]
I don’t think so.

37:20.572 --> 37:23.405
Booth’s father was a barber.
He knows his hair.

37:23.492 --> 37:26.234
- And ljust found blood.
- [ Booth ] Blood.

37:26.328 --> 37:28.660
Bones, get off the chair,
will you? Blood.

37:28.747 --> 37:31.363
Based on how he was
positioned in the sink,

37:31.458 --> 37:34.245
it’s no surprise Santiago’s blood
spurted this high.

37:34.336 --> 37:36.201
Well, you forgot to clean
that area up there.

37:41.301 --> 37:43.713
I just wanted my own chair.

37:45.347 --> 37:47.633
I begged him.

37:47.724 --> 37:50.932
After everything
I did for Santiago, he just—

37:51.019 --> 37:52.680
he just laughed at me.

37:52.771 --> 37:55.353
So you scalped him?
What, killing him wasn’t enough?

37:56.692 --> 38:01.061
His hair was—
It was so beautiful.

38:12.166 --> 38:15.408
It was the most beautiful hair
I had ever cut.

38:16.670 --> 38:18.706
So you kept it.

38:37.483 --> 38:40.771
Mr. Vaziri, you’re here quite late.

38:40.861 --> 38:44.445
Oh, lwasjust thinking.
I guess I lost track of time.

38:45.741 --> 38:47.652
You got a long life
ahead of you.

38:47.743 --> 38:50.610
You’ll publish.
Don’t worry.

38:50.704 --> 38:53.320
I wasn’t supposed to tell anyone,
but I told everyone.

38:53.415 --> 38:55.121
And then my parents
told everyone.

38:55.209 --> 38:57.291
And they told everyone.

38:57.377 --> 38:59.709
It was like a chain letter of
embarrassment and humiliation.

38:59.796 --> 39:02.333
You know you were
instrumental in solving
this case, right?

39:02.424 --> 39:04.585
l was just doing what
Dr. Brennan told me to.

39:04.676 --> 39:06.507
She trusted your ability.

39:06.595 --> 39:09.928
I’ve never seen her
leave an intern alone
at that stage in a case.

39:16.188 --> 39:17.678
I was thinking—

39:17.773 --> 39:20.515
“Tactile Forensic Detection
of Bone Anomalies
in the Digital Age.”

39:20.609 --> 39:23.146
That could be
a fascinating paper,
don’t you think?

39:23.237 --> 39:25.228
Oh, go watch some TV,
Mr. Vaziri.

39:25.364 --> 39:27.355
Take the night off.
Right.

39:50.180 --> 39:51.386
[Crickets Chirping ]

39:51.473 --> 39:54.260
[ Brennan ]
So, it turned out that Kevin
was actually telling the truth?

39:54.351 --> 39:57.013
Yeah. Theo stole
the antifreeze from his car
to burn the body.

39:57.104 --> 39:59.561
You know, it turns out that Kevin
is a pretty honest guy,

39:59.648 --> 40:02.640
you know, for a—
a miserable drug dealer.

40:02.776 --> 40:05.813
She’s still asleep?
She is. Look at that, huh?

40:05.946 --> 40:09.188
She’s like a tiny
drunken sailor in a Onesie.
[ Both Laugh ]

40:09.283 --> 40:12.491
She actually
let us finish a whole meal,
one that didn’t get cold.

40:12.578 --> 40:14.534
You think we should
push it with dessert?

40:14.663 --> 40:17.450
Sure.
I’ll get some ice cream.
Ice cream!

40:17.541 --> 40:19.702
I scream for ice cream.
I’ll have chocolate.

40:19.793 --> 40:21.374
That’d be good.

40:21.461 --> 40:23.588
- Don’t forget the chocolate.
- Of course I’ll get chocolate.

40:23.672 --> 40:25.162
Yeah.

40:26.592 --> 40:27.877
Here we go.
Look at that.

40:28.010 --> 40:30.626
Oh, what is—
What is this?
It’s a present.

40:30.762 --> 40:32.548
For me?
Yeah.

40:32.681 --> 40:34.888
[ Chuckles ]
Thank you.
Mm-hmm.

40:34.975 --> 40:36.215
Why?

40:36.310 --> 40:39.017
Well, you know,
’cause l-l love you, I guess.

40:39.104 --> 40:41.516
You guess?
[ Chuckles ]

40:43.400 --> 40:46.016
[Paper Crinkling]

40:46.111 --> 40:47.851
Oh.

40:47.988 --> 40:49.774
Lingerie.
Lingerie. Huh? Look.

40:49.865 --> 40:52.026
Three pieces.
It matches, okay?
There’s a bralette.

40:52.117 --> 40:54.324
There’s a—
a negligee and a tanga.

40:54.411 --> 40:57.619
Tanga. That’s a seaport
in northern Tanzania.

40:57.706 --> 40:59.992
Well, I must’ve misunderstood
what she said then.

41:00.083 --> 41:02.699
Booth, why did you
buy me lingerie?

41:02.794 --> 41:04.785
You were complaining,
you know, earlier about...

41:04.880 --> 41:06.996
how your clothes
haven’t been fitting you...

41:07.090 --> 41:08.955
and you don’t feel right
about yourself,

41:09.051 --> 41:11.042
so Ijust thought
that, uh, you know—

41:11.136 --> 41:14.094
I complain because
it’s an irritating inconvenience,

41:14.181 --> 41:17.389
not because I’m unhappy
with the way I look.

41:17.476 --> 41:19.558
Are you unhappy
with the way I look?

41:19.645 --> 41:21.306
No, no.

41:21.396 --> 41:23.478
There are hormonal
and physiological changes...

41:23.565 --> 41:26.022
that the body goes through
after childbirth.

41:26.109 --> 41:27.940
It’s a fascinating process,
but for some men,

41:28.028 --> 41:31.020
those changes could make them
lose interest in their mates.

41:31.114 --> 41:32.615
Well, they don’t live with you.

41:39.456 --> 41:40.946
[Chuckling]

41:42.709 --> 41:45.576
I’ve never had undergarments
like these before.

41:45.671 --> 41:48.287
They seem very comfortable.

41:48.423 --> 41:50.334
You chose well.
Yeah?

41:50.425 --> 41:51.676
Mm-hmm.

41:51.760 --> 41:53.876
Maybe we should go upstairs
so I can try them on.

41:53.970 --> 41:56.427
Well, comfort is what
I was thinking about.
Purely comfort.

41:56.556 --> 41:59.548
Mm-hmm.
Right? I should put this away
so it doesn’t melt.

41:59.685 --> 42:01.516
No, Booth.
Yeah?

42:01.645 --> 42:04.261
Let it melt.
Whoa!

42:04.356 --> 42:07.268
Or we could just take it with us.
I’ll take it with us.

42:07.359 --> 42:08.690
[Laughs]

42:08.777 --> 42:11.143
[Christine Crying]

42:12.280 --> 42:14.236
Okay, you know what?
I’ll— I’ll change her.

42:14.324 --> 42:16.736
Okay, but I’m still
going to put this on.

42:16.827 --> 42:18.658
Yeah. Okay.

42:19.788 --> 42:21.278
I’m still bringing this.

42:21.373 --> 42:23.113
You’ll get it
sticky though.

42:23.208 --> 42:26.325
You know, sometimes sticky—
Depends on where you put it.

43:00.287 --> 43:01.652
What’s that mean?

43:03.582 --> 43:04.571
English - US - PSDH
